race.comment: HARDPOINT (5) returned five weeks ago with a brave second over 1400m at Kembla, just going under after a fierce battle with the winner. Kept up to the mark with a subsequent trial. Has a fine second-up record and can add to that today. MASTER RILEY (3) darted through on the rails late and just missed out in a real thriller over 1400m at Warwick Farm last time out. Has a couple of wins and a placing from three Newcastle runs. Very fit and peaking for this. Track specialist GENERAL SOHO (1) resumed with a modest effort in a quality sprint at Port Macquarie recently. Nicely in after the claim and gets the right run from the inside stall so his prospects are bright. ORTHIE'S BOYS (4) was runner-up in a BM64 here at this trip last time to continue a long run of strong form. Must be considered again. DJAPANA (11) recorded his best first-up performance when beaten a whisker over 1400m at Kembla last start. Back in fine shape and can build on that.
